Some Important Key Points:

1. This project is made via using IDE named as IntelliJ Idea
2. In the Dependency folder there is a Chrome Driver (ver.117.0)
3. If you have previous version of chromedriver you can replace it with your own current using one
4. JDK version 19.0 was used in this framework
5. In Step Definition file there are 2 methods i.e "PageObject.chromeConfig()" and "PageObject.edgeConfig()"
    You can use either of the 2 as by default i have enabled chromeConfig so the test will run on chrome
    If you enable edgeConfig it will run the test on Edge browser

To Execute The Test:

1. Simply navigate to src/test/java/RunTest.java
2. Open the file and execute it

To View Steps:

1. Simply navigate to src/test/java/step_defs/task_steps.java
2. Open the file and view all the steps

To View Page Object Model:

1. Simply navigate to src/test/java/POM/PageObject.java
2. Open the file and view all the Page Object Models methods and there are also comments mention so that the person viewing can understand

To View Features File:

1. Simply navigate to src/test/resources/task.feature
2. Open the file and you can view gherkin syntax

After Executing the Test an allure folder will be generated with .json files in it, you can view them in the browser.